# ORIG TITLE    Denmark’s folksy ballad wins Eurovision . 
# ORIG CONTENT  She had been the favourite, and in the end, there were no ‘teardrops’ on her face as Emmelie de Forrest made it a third Eurovision win for Denmark. “Of course I believed in the song and I thought we had a great song but that’s the exciting thing with Eurovision, you never know what’s going to happen and I was dying in the Green Room. It was so exciting with the points and it was so close, so I was very surprised and shocked when it happened”, said Emmelie de Forrest the Eurovision winner, speaking in Malmö . The competition comes to Copenhagen next year, but before then – a long night of partying! . 
